Order by Clause
---------------
-The order by clause is used to sort the result set of query by one or more column.

-It can sort the results in ascending or descending order.

-We will use ASC for ascending order and DESC for descending order.

-If we donâ€™t specify sort order, the default sort order is ascending.

Syntax:-
--------
        SELECT * FROM tablename ORDER BY columnname [ASC/DESC]
        SELECT * FROM tablename ORDER BY col1[ASC/DESC], col2[ASC/DESC]

        
        Single column ascending order
        -----------------------------
Sql:
        SELECT * FROM Employees ORDER BY id;
        SELECT * FROM Employees ORDER BY id ASC;

  | id | first_name | last_name | department_id | salary | years_worked |
  |----|------------|-----------|---------------|--------|--------------|
  | 2  | Clarence   | Robinson  | 1             | 3617   | 2            |
